  "claims": [
    {
      "statement": "Package-writer executable/matrix schema v1 isolate file-backed minizip-ng package entry writes, and Patch executable schema v15/matrix v9 add configured file buffer, writer input peak, writer call count and maximum writer-call wall-time telemetry while retaining prior Patch telemetry.",
      "artifact_paths": [
        "isolated-forward-formula-matrix.json",
        "isolated-forward-mixed-inline-matrix.json",
        "isolated-forward-numeric-matrix.json",
        "patch-v15-formula-hyperlink-matrix.json",
        "patch-v15-mixed-inline-matrix.json",
        "patch-v15-numeric-matrix.json",
        "summary.json"
      ]
    },
    {
      "statement": "On this machine and the recorded one-million-cell level-1 isolated writer workloads, 512 KiB reduced combined target-entry median by 4.30% for numeric, 5.06% for mixed-inline and 0.85% for formula versus 1 MiB, reduced median maximum writer-call wall time by 41.65%-53.26%, and reduced process peak working set by about 0.99 MiB.",
      "artifact_paths": [
        "isolated-forward-formula-matrix.json",
        "isolated-forward-mixed-inline-matrix.json",
        "isolated-forward-numeric-matrix.json",
        "isolated-reverse-formula-matrix.json",
        "isolated-reverse-mixed-inline-matrix.json",
        "isolated-reverse-numeric-matrix.json",
        "summary.json"
      ]
    },
    {
      "statement": "Numeric and mixed-inline improved in both ascending and descending buffer orders; formula improved by 2.76% in ascending order and regressed by 0.43% in descending order. The 2 MiB and 4 MiB cases did not provide stable cross-workload gains and used more process peak working set, so no universal throughput claim is made.",
      "artifact_paths": [
        "isolated-forward-formula-matrix.json",
        "isolated-forward-mixed-inline-matrix.json",
        "isolated-forward-numeric-matrix.json",
        "isolated-reverse-formula-matrix.json",
        "isolated-reverse-mixed-inline-matrix.json",
        "isolated-reverse-numeric-matrix.json",
        "summary.json"
      ]
    },
    {
      "statement": "Patch schema v15/matrix v9 confirmed a 512 KiB writer input peak, 1 MiB two-buffer prefetch peak, staged CRC reuse and bounded call traffic for numeric, mixed-inline and formula-plus-external-hyperlink upsert outputs. Production/stored CTest passed 132/132, no-images and three install consumers passed, 18 representative outputs opened with openpyxl 3.1.2, Office was not run, and no cross-machine, arbitrary-workbook, pure-encoder, full-feature or OpenXLSX-superiority claim is made.",
